{"metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.13","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"role":"article"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture now provides first class tools for building features in UIKit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"including minimal state observation, presentation and stack navigation.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is now integrated with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-navigation","isActive":true},{"text":" library,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which brings powerful navigation and observation tools to UIKit. You can model your domains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as concisely as possible, just as you would in SwiftUI, but then implement your view in UIKit","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"without losing any power.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The simplest tool to use is ","type":"text"},{"code":"observe","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which allows you to minimally observe changes to state in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"your feature and update the UI. Typically the best place to do this is in ","type":"text"},{"code":"viewDidLoad","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let store: StoreOf<Feature>","","func viewDidLoad() {","  super.viewDidLoad()","","  \/\/ ...","","  observe { [weak self] in","    countLabel.text = \"Count: \\(store.count)\"","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Only the state accessed in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"observe","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" trailing closure will be observed. If any other state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes, the closure will not be invoked and no extra work will be performed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The library also provides powerful navigation tools for UIKit. For example, suppose you have a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"feature that can present a child feature (see the docs on ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"tree-based","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigation","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TreeBasedNavigation","overridingTitle":"tree-based navigation"},{"text":" for more information on these tools):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Reducer ","struct Feature {","  @ObservableState","  struct State {","    @Presents var child: ChildFeature.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Then you can present a view controller when the child state flips to a non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value by using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"present(item:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" API that comes with the library:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@UIBindable var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","func viewDidLoad() {","  super.viewDidLoad()","","  present(item: $store.scope(state: \\.child, action: \\.child)) { store in","    ChildViewController(store: store)","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, if your feature has a stack of features that can be presented, then you can model your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"domain like so (see the docs on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackBasedNavigation","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"stack-based","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"stack-based"}]},{"text":" for more information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on these tools):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Reducer","struct AppFeature {","  struct State {","    var path = StackState<Path.State>()","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  @Reducer","  enum Path {","    case addItem(AddFeature)","    case detailItem(DetailFeature)","    case editItem(EditFeature)","  }","","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"And for the view you can subclass ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStackController"},{"text":" in order to drive navigation from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stack state:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["class AppController: NavigationStackController {","  private var store: StoreOf<AppFeature>!","","  convenience init(store: StoreOf<AppFeature>) {","    @UIBindable var store = store","","    self.init(path: $store.scope(state: \\.path, action: \\.path)) {","      RootViewController(store: store)","    } destination: { store in ","      switch store.case {","      case .addItem(let store):","        AddViewController(store: store)","      case .detailItem(let store):","        DetailViewController(store: store)","      case .editItem(let store):","        EditViewController(store: store)","      }","    }","","    self.store = store","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.13"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.17.1":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"The Sharing library has graduated, with backwards-incompatible changes, to 2.0, and the Composable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Architecture has been updated to extend support to this new version.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.1